result.execSummary:
The defendant Tiffanie D. Steele was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tiffanie D. Steele is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tiffanie D. Steele was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tiffanie D. Steele in court.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the parties have resolution today.  Atty Hendee states that the defendant has paid $275.00 in full today.    Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 2. Ct. 1 to be dismissed.  Atty Hendee asks that restitution be ordered to be paid out by the COC office.
Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees.    Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.    Defendant waives their right to an attorney and wants to proceed.    Court finds waiver made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 2.  Ct. 1 to be dismissed.
